The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 October is 3,693 (427.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 October, there were 225 new confirmed cases (26.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 September, there were 139 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 62% (86 extra cases).
